-- t25. Between Two Fascisms: Language Brings Everything to Light -- t26. Headlong into Servitude: When Madmen Lead the Blind -- t27. Out of the Abyss: Prussian Eagles and Parched Tongues -- t28. Where Lawlessness Makes Law Its Instrument -- t29. Prophets of Doom and the Triumph of Aryan Teutonism -- tNotes -- tGlossary and Index0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe first complete English translation of a far-seeing polemic, written in 1933 by the preeminent German-language satirist, unmasking the Nazi seizure of power Now available in English for the first time, Austrian satirist and polemicist Karl Kraus’s Third Walpurgis Night was written in immediate response to the Nazi seizure of power in 1933 but withheld from publication for fear of reprisals against Jews trapped in Germany. Acclaimed when finally published by Kösel Verlag in 1952, it is a devastatingly prescient exposure, giving special attention to the regime’s corruption of language as masterminded by Joseph Goebbels. Bertolt Brecht wrote to Kraus that, in his indictment of Nazism, “You have disclosed the atrocities of intonation and created an ethics of language.” This masterful translation, by the prizewinning translators of Kraus’s The Last Days of Mankind, aims for clarity where Kraus had good reason to be cautious and obscure.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aNational socialism. 0aPolitical satire, German. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Essays.2bisacsh1 aBridgham, Fred.1 aPerloff, Marjorie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPerloff, Marjorie.1 aTimms, Edward.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z97831